 The question is asking for the number of characters used in the content. LENGTH() returns the length of the string measured in bytes.
LENGTH() returns the length of the string measured in bytes.

SELECT tweet_id
FROM Tweets
WHERE LENGTH (content) > '15';

CHAR_LENGTH() returns the length of the string measured in characters.
This is especially relevant for Unicode, in which most characters are encoded in two bytes, or UTF-8, where the number of bytes varies.
